        "instruction": "Fill in the blanks to complete the if statement based on the Java Basics Quiz Essentials. Refer to the learning cards for guidance.",
        "codeTemplate": "if (x ___ 10) { System.out.println(\"x is ___\"); } else { System.out.println(\"x is not 10\"); }",
        "options": [
          "==",
          "!=",
          ">", 
          "<"
        ],
        "correctAnswer": "==,10",
        "explanation": "In Java, the if statement checks if x is equal to 10, and executes the corresponding block of code."
      },
      {
        "instruction": "Complete the else statement based on what you learned about Java control structures.",
        "codeTemplate": "if (x ___ 5) { System.out.println(\"x is greater than 5\"); } else { System.out.println(\"x is ___\"); }",
        "options": [
          "<",
          ">=",
          "==", 
          "!="
        ],
        "correctAnswer": "<,5",
        "explanation": "The else statement executes when the condition in the if statement is false, providing an alternative output."
      }
    ]
  }
